The letter "A" first appears in the spelling of the number **"ten"** (which is written as "10"). However, since "10" uses the digit "1" and "0," not the letter "A," we must look for the first whole number whose name (in English) contains the letter "A."

Let's list the numbers and their names:

1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9 — none have an "A" in their names.

Ten — "ten" (no "A").

Eleven — "eleven" (no "A").

Twelve — "twelve" (no "A").

Thirteen — "thirteen" (no "A").

Fourteen — "fourteen" (no "A").

Fifteen — "fifteen" (no "A").

Sixteen — "sixteen" (no "A").

Seventeen — "seventeen" (no "A").

Eighteen — "eighteen" (no "A").

