**3. Write a short story of the three little pigs who met the little red riding hood.**

Once upon a time, three little pigs set out to build houses. The first pig built his house of straw. It was quick to build but soon tumbled down when the wind blew.

The second pig built his house of sticks. It was stronger than straw but still not sturdy enough; the sticks crumbled when the next big storm came.

The third pig, being clever, decided to build his house of bricks. It took a long time, but it was the sturdiest house of all and stood strong against any storm.

As the pigs were resting, a beautiful girl named Red Riding Hood wandered through the forest. She was looking for her grandmother, who lived nearby. The third pig, hearing her footsteps, opened the door and greeted Red Riding Hood.

At that moment, the big bad wolf, who had been lurking outside, saw the bright red cloak and tried to sneak in. Red Riding Hood, noticing the wolf, asked him where he was going. The wolf tried to trick her, saying he was going to her grandmother's house to ask for aporridge. Red Riding Hood followed the wolf, but when she saw his true face, she ran back to the house and closed the door.

The clever third pig had set a trap. He left a plate of porridge at the door with a straw in it. The wolf ate the porridge and tried to swallow the straw, but it got stuck. The pigs came and caught the wolf, saving them all from danger.

From that day on, the third pig was known as the wisest and bravest of all the pigs, and Red Riding Hood learned to always be careful in the forest.

And they all lived happily ever after. [end of text]


